Yes, I can explain what are end-of-line comments and block comments in OpenROAD:
End-of-line comments begin with "//" and are used to comment out a single line or the ends of partial lines. Here's an example:
//This is an end-of-line comment
Block comments begin with "/*" and end with "*/" and may include multiple lines. They are used to provide information about your code, such as what it does or why you wrote certain code in a particular way. Here's an example:
/* This is a multi-line block
comment. */

Here are some examples of how block comments are used in OpenROAD:
1. To document the purpose and functionality of a function, procedure, or trigger. For example:
```
/* This function takes two arguments (a date and a duration) and returns the end date */
function EndDate(date, duration);
```
2. To explain code that is not self-explanatory. For example:
```
/* Check to see if this customer has already received this promotion */
if (customerPromotions.exists(promotionId)) {
    // Promotion has been previously awarded
    return false;
}
```
3. To prevent the misuse or misunderstanding of code. For example:
```
/* This trigger should never be disabled or deleted! */
create trigger onUpdateOrderStatus(update);
```
